There is a large disparity in automobile costs, with certain brands selling for more than others, according to descriptive statistics. According to inferential statistics, the car age and mileage are significant determinants of automobile costs, with newer and lower-mileage vehicles often costing more. Another important factor is brand; luxury products usually command greater pricing than economical brands. For the actionable items we can implement dynamic pricing strategies based on age and mileage to optimize revenue.Focus on acquiring and selling popular brands or models to capitalize on market demand.To draw in customers on a tight budget, provide reasonable prices for vehicles with higher mileage or older models. For the next Steps and recommendations we can further explore the relationship between car condition and prices to refine pricing strategies. Consider incorporating additional external factors such as economic indicators or seasonal trends to improve price predictions.Create a strong pricing model with machine learning approaches to boost market competitiveness and automate price choices.
